The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing sparse signals from one-bit quantized measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new penalty function and an iterative algorithm for solving the problem, which are related to optimization and machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.SI (Systems and Control) are also possible sub-categories.
